  "notes": "Sranan Tongo (Sranantongo), the English-lexifier creole lingua franca of Suriname, with heavy Dutch and West African (Gbe, Kikongo) input. The mapping follows the official 1986 phonology-based spelling: ⟨ò⟩ = /ɔ/, ⟨sy⟩ = /ʃ/, ⟨ty dy⟩ = /t͡ʃ d͡ʒ/, ⟨aw ow⟩ = the diphthongs /au̯ ou̯/. Older Dutch-influenced spellings are common in the wild and are not handled. English is the lexifier, not an ancestor node in this graph.",
